Class DnCRecursivePrimitiveAction.DnCRecursiveLongAction

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.concurrent.ForkJoinTask<java.lang.Void>
      • java.util.concurrent.RecursiveAction

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.util.concurrent.Future<java.lang.Void>
    Enclosing class:
    DnCRecursivePrimitiveAction

    public abstract static class DnCRecursivePrimitiveAction.DnCRecursiveLongAction
extends java.util.concurrent.RecursiveAction
    The DnCRecursiveLongAction class provides a "divide-and-conquer" RecursiveTask which deals with long values. By making it an "action", autoboxing (which would be forced by a RecursiveTask<Long>'s use of the object equivalent Long class) is avoided and all tasks/actions can deal explicitly with primitive values. For more information on primitive action divide-and-conquer strategies and idioms, see the documentation for the DnCRecursivePrimitiveAction class.
